    .content
      h2 Overview for Developers
      section#libraries
        h3 Libraries
        p
          | Enketo maintains 4 libraries that can be used to build an Enketo-powered application. 
          | The illustration below shows how these 4 libraries are used as building blocks of one such application: Enketo Express.

        .dev-overview
          h4 Enketo Express
          ul 
             li communication with OpenRosa server
             li persistent storage in browser
             li applicationCache in browser
          .dev-overview__2nd
            .dev-overview__2nd__side client
            h4 Enketo Core
            ul 
              li form rendering
              li form logic
              li form API
            .dev-overview__3rd
              h4 Enketo XPathJS
              ul 
                li XPath evaluation
          .dev-overview__2nd
            .dev-overview__2nd__side server
            h4 Enketo Transformer
            ul 
              li XSL transformation of XForm
              li markdown processsing
              li language directionality
              li media/data resource URI resolution
            .dev-overview__3rd
              h4 Enketo XSLT
              ul
                li XSL stylesheets

        p These libraries are divided in a logical way so they can be used for light-weight mobile hybrid applications, as well as web applications. There is a lot of flexibility in using these libraries. For example you could use Enketo XSLT in your own transformer in the language of your choice. 

      section#transformation
        h3 Transformation
        p.
          Enketo's form engine, Enketo Core, does not read XForms directly. It works with the result of a transformation of an 
          XForm into a JSON object containing a form HTML string and a model XML string.
          The illustration below gives a high-level overview of this transformation.

        .dev-transformation
          .dev-transformation__main
            .dev-transformation__main__part
              .dev-transformation__main__part__side XForm instances
              :md
                ```xml
                <model>
                  <instance>
                    <data>
                      <node/>
                      <resp/>
                    </data>
                  </instance>
                  <instance id="countries"/>
                  ...
                </model>
                ```
            .dev-transformation__main__part
              .dev-transformation__main__part__side XForm binds
              :md
                ```xml
                <bind 
                  nodeset="/data/node" 
                  relevant="/data/resp = 'a'"
                  constraint=". > 6"
                  type="integer"
                />
                ```
            .dev-transformation__main__part
                .dev-transformation__main__part__side XForm body
                :md
                  ```xml
                  <input 
                    ref="/data/node"
                    appearance="distress"
                  >
                    <label>Enter Number</label>
                  </input>
                  ```
          .dev-transformation__arrow
            i.fa.fa-arrow-right 
          .dev-transformation__main
            .dev-transformation__main__part
              .dev-transformation__main__part__side XML instances
              :md
                ```xml  
                <model>
                  <instance>
                    <data>
                      <node/>
                      <resp/>
                    </data>
                  </instance>
                  <instance id="countries"/>
                  ...
                </model>
                ```
            .dev-transformation__main__part
              .dev-transformation__main__part__side HTML form
              :md
                ```xml
                <form class="or">
                  <label 
                    class="...-distress"
                  >
                    <span>Enter Number</span>
                    <input
                      type="number"
                      name="/data/node"
                      data-relevant="/data/resp= 'a'"
                      data-constraint=". > 6"
                      data-type-xml="integer"
                    />
                  </label>
                </form>
                ```
        :md
          The transformation uses [XSL](https://www.w3.org/Style/XSL/) and could theoretically be performed by any XSL Transformer in any language. 
          It's been confirmed to work in PHP and NodeJS.
